In any graph $G$, a path (resp. cycle) that contains every vertex of $G$ is called a \emph{Hamilton path} (resp. \emph{Hamilton cycle}) of $G$. A graph is \emph{traceable} if it contains a Hamilton path, and a graph is \emph{hamiltonian} if it contains a Hamilton cycle. The following is an immediate consequence of these definitions as well as Proposition \ref{lowerbound}.

